# PRICE Workshop Website Rules

## Project Structure
- The website is built using Hugo static site generator
- Content is stored in the `content/` directory with Markdown files
- Layouts are in the `layouts/` directory
- Assets (CSS, JS) are in the `assets/` directory

## Key Files and Their Purpose
- `content/_index.md` - Main homepage content
- `content/call-for-submissions.md` - Call for submissions page
- `layouts/_default/baseof.html` - Base layout template with header and footer
- `hugo.toml` - Hugo configuration file

## How to Add New Pages
1. Create a new Markdown file in the `content/` directory
2. Add proper front matter with title and other metadata
3. Include content in Markdown format
4. The site will automatically generate the page based on Hugo's layout system

## How to Update Content
- For main content changes, modify the relevant Markdown files in `content/`
- For layout changes, modify files in `layouts/`
- For styling, modify files in `assets/`

## Adding New Features
1. When adding new functionality, always check existing patterns in the codebase
2. Maintain consistent formatting and structure
3. Ensure all new pages are properly linked from existing pages
4. Test the build process with `hugo` command before committing

## Repository Rules
- Always commit changes with descriptive messages
- Keep the project structure consistent with existing patterns
- Update documentation when adding new features or changing behavior
- Test website build before finalizing changes

## Development Workflow
1. Make changes to content or code
2. Test locally with `hugo server` or `hugo` command
3. Commit changes with clear, descriptive messages
4. Push to remote repository

## Common Commands
- `hugo` - Build the website
- `hugo server` - Start local development server
- `git status` - Check current changes
- `git add .` - Stage all changes
- `git commit -m "message"` - Commit changes